==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wight
<hw>Wight</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wight</ets>,
<ets>wiht</ets>, a wight, a whit, AS. <ets>wiht</ets>, <ets>wuht</ets>,
a creature, a thing; skin to D. <ets>wicht</ets> a child, OS. & OHG.
<ets>wiht</ets> a creature, thing, G. <ets>wicht</ets> a creature, Icel.
<ets>v⟦ae⟧tt<?/</ets> a wight, <ets>v⟦ae⟧tt<?/</ets> a whit, Goth.
<ets>wa⟦iacute⟧hts</ets>, <ets>wa⟦iacute⟧ht</ets>, thing; cf. Russ.
<ets>veshche</ets> a thing. <?/. Cf. <er>Whit</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A whit; a bit; a jot.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She was fallen asleep a little <qex>wight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A supernatural being.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A human being; a person, either male or female; --
now used chiefly in irony or burlesque, or in humorous language.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Worst of all <xex>wightes</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every <qex>wight</qex> that hath discretion.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Oh, say me true if thou wert mortal <qex>wight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wight</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wight
<hw>Wight</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wight</ets>,
<ets>wiht</ets>, probably of Scand. origin; cf. Icel.
<ets>v⟦imac⟧gr</ets> in fighting condition, neut. <ets>v⟦imac⟧gh
<?/<?/<?/ v⟦imac⟧g</ets> war, akin to AS. <ets>w⟦imac⟧g</ets> See
<er>Vanquish</er>.]</ety> <def>Swift; nimble; agile; strong and
active.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is full <qex>wight</qex>, God wot, as is a roe.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was so wimble and so <qex>wight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were Night and Day, and Day and Night,⟦br⟧
Pilgrims <qex>wight</qex> with steps forthright.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wightly</ent>⟦br⟧
